url: "https://kganitis.github.io/bam-engine/"
license: MIT
doi: "10.5281/zenodo.17610305"

abstract: |
  BAM Engine is a high-performance Python framework that implements the BAM
  (Bottom-Up Adaptive Macroeconomics) agent-based model from "Macroeconomics
  from the Bottom-up" (Delli Gatti et al., 2011). The model simulates
  interactions between households, firms, and banks across labor, credit, and
  consumption goods markets. The framework features an Entity-Component-System
  (ECS) architecture with vectorized operations for performance and a modular
  extension system. It includes built-in validation and calibration tools to
  support reproducible computational economics research.

keywords:
